caption:
Table 1. Performance evaluation on the DAVIS [21] benchmark. 
First: IoU score for region similarity (higher is better). Second: 
F-measure (higher is better) for contour accuracy. Stability is de-
noted by the mean standard deviation of each metric (lower is bet-
ter). At the end of the table, we present the approximate process-
ing time for each method as reported in earlier work

Table 2. Performance evaluation on the SegTrack [13] benchmark 
using IoU score (higher is better). Red: best , blue: second best.

Table 3. Errors on the JumpCut [7] benchmark using a transfer 
distance of sixteen (lower is better). Red: best , blue: second best.

Table 4. Error rate (lower is better) evaluation on the Thermal-
Road [32] benchmark. Red: best , blue: second best.
